HEADWORD: Nomopelmous
<hw>Nom`o*pel"mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>no`mos</grk> law, custom + <?/ sole of the foot.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a separate and simple tendon to flex the
first toe, or hallux, as do passerine birds.</def>⟦br⟧
